    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-11-16T10:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-11-16T10:16:00-05:00" n="557"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">871.6363/248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-11-16T17:00:00+01:44">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1924—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 17—4:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Arrived Bucharest Sunday night.<note n="51" xml:id="d557fn51">Nov. 9.</note>
                    Court, Government and unofficial circles seem apparently genuinely pleased by my
                    return. I explained while personally glad to be back our affairs are far from
                    being settled.</p>
                <p>Have so far merely made short courtesy call on Minister for Foreign Affairs who
                    has been absent with King in Bukowina during the week, preferring if possible to
                    await receipt of Department’s instruction now en route.<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d557fn52">Department’s instruction no. 319, Nov. 7, <ref
                            target="#pg_637">p. 637</ref>.</note> As I now learn instructions cannot
                    arrive before 25th I contemplate seeing Minister for Foreign Affairs beginning
                    of the week regarding Baldwin matter and 15–30 meter distance mining-law
                    regulation, subject recent American and British protests.</p>
                <p>I had yesterday audience with the King lasting one hour. His Majesty extremely
                    friendly and apparently familiar with our affairs. <pb facs="0738" n="644"
                        xml:id="pg_644"/> His Majesty then discussed the Baldwin case. See my number
                    77, November 16, 7 p.m.<note n="53" xml:id="d557fn53">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
